PRESIDENT Cyril Ramaphosa has announced Siyabonga Cwele as
new minister of Home Affairs and Nomvula Mokonyane as the Environmental affairs
minister. Ramaphosa says the Tele communication ministry will be
merged with the Communication ministry which will be led by Stella
Ndabeni-Abrahams. The President also announce that Thembi Majola will be resigning
as deputy minister of the Energy department as from January to attend to family
matters. 